<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="129" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="129">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miq. first published in Fl. Ned. Ind. 1 (2): 630" authorityYear="1859" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Mangifera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mangifera sumatrana" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sumatrana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Mangifera sumatrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been considered as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Mangifera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mangifera laurina" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laurina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Mangifera laurina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bl. The distinctive characteristics of the 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. sumatrana" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sumatrana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">M. sumatrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are panicles pyramidal and not dense, large and flat fruit, prominent fruit beak type, a quantity of fibre in pulp and high stone. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. laurina" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laurina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">M. laurina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
panicles are conical and dense, with small and thick fruit, round in shape and fruit break type is perceptible (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Mangifera sumatrana A habit B adaxial and abaxial surface of leaf C pyramidal panicles D flowers E flowers after anthesis; F ovary with swollen disc G roundish fruit H flattened fruit I pulp." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.199.80727.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/693718" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Mangifera laurina A conical panicles B flowers C roundish thick fruit." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.199.80727.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/693719" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
